 confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":20,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705197,"age":93,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Plowfield was born about 1362, in England as the daughter of Hugh Plowfield. She had at least 1 son with John Pembridge."},"et":{"ABT 1362–":"umbes 1362–Surnud","1362–Female":"1362–Surnud","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","1388–Male":"1388–Surnud","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","ABT 1362":"umbes 1362","1335":"1335","1455":"1455","1388":"1388","1362":"1362","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","England":"England","Pembridge, Herefordshire, England":"Pembridge, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1362–":"noin 1362–Kuollut","1362–Female":"1362–Kuollut","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","1388–Male":"1388–Kuollut","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","ABT 1362":"noin 1362","1335":"1335","1455":"1455","1388":"1388","1362":"1362","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","England":"England","Pemb